# Security Rules

## URL Handling

- ALL user-provided URLs must pass through `normalizeLink()` from `@excalidraw/common` (uses @braintree/sanitize-url)
- For URL validation use `toValidURL()` — returns `"about:blank"` for invalid URLs
- Never construct href attributes from raw user input
- Source: `packages/common/src/url.ts`

## Embeddable Content & Iframes

- Embeddable URLs are validated against a strict domain whitelist in `packages/element/src/embeddable.ts`
- Do NOT add domains to `ALLOWED_DOMAINS` or `ALLOW_SAME_ORIGIN` without explicit security review
- Iframe srcdoc content must use `escapeDoubleQuotes()` for embedded URLs
- Always specify `targetOrigin` in `postMessage()` calls — never use `"*"`
- Validate `event.origin` on all `message` event handlers

## SVG Export

- Use proper DOM APIs (`createElementNS` with `SVG_NS`) — never string concatenation or innerHTML for SVG
- Sanitize all link hrefs with `normalizeLink()` before embedding in SVG output
- Validate embed links via `getEmbedLink()` with domain whitelist before rendering
- Source: `packages/excalidraw/renderer/staticSvgScene.ts`

## File Import & Images

- Validate actual MIME types by checking file magic bytes (`getActualMimeTypeFromImage()`) — do not trust file extensions alone
- Use `isSupportedImageFile()` guard before processing any image
- Validate Excalidraw data structure with `isValidExcalidrawData()` before restoring
- Library URLs are restricted to the whitelist in `packages/excalidraw/data/library.ts` — do not bypass `validateLibraryUrl()`
- Source: `packages/excalidraw/data/blob.ts`, `packages/excalidraw/data/image.ts`

## Encryption

- Use AES-GCM via Web Crypto API (`packages/excalidraw/data/encryption.ts`) — do not introduce custom crypto
- IVs must be generated with `crypto.getRandomValues()`, never reused
- Do not change `ENCRYPTION_KEY_BITS` (128) without security review

## Forbidden Patterns

- No `eval()`, `new Function()`, or `document.write()`
- No `dangerouslySetInnerHTML` with user-provided content (existing QRCode usage is safe — internally generated SVG only)
- No `innerHTML` with user-controlled strings
- No disabling of iframe sandbox attributes
- No `postMessage` with `targetOrigin: "*"`

## Environment & Secrets

- Never commit `.env` files with private keys or credentials
- Firebase config and RSA public keys in `.env.*` are intentionally public (client-side)
- Do NOT add server-side secrets to `.env.production` or `.env.development`

## How to verify

- `grep -rn "eval\b\|new Function\|document\.write" packages/ --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx"` — must return nothing
- `grep -rn "dangerouslySetInnerHTML" packages/ --include="*.tsx"` — only QRCode.tsx (internally generated SVG)
- `grep -rn "innerHTML" packages/ --include="*.ts" --include="*.tsx"` — audit each usage for user-controlled input
- `grep -rn "targetOrigin.*\*" packages/ excalidraw-app/` — must return nothing (no wildcard postMessage)
- `grep -rn "normalizeLink\|toValidURL" packages/excalidraw/renderer/` — confirm SVG export sanitizes URLs
- `yarn test:app --watch=false` — URL sanitization tests in `packages/common/tests/url.test.tsx` pass